}}{{TIDTOC|adapter}} ==Overview== "F5U101" and the '''Belkin''' logo is silkscreened on the board. :The '''TI''' hub IC is marked with "TUSB2046B", "1AT", and "A7VX". :In addition to the '''TI''' hub IC, the device uses '''Tocon''' capacitors, a TRB-5VDC-SB3-CD relay, two [http://www.micrel.com/_PDF/mic2026.pdf '''Micrel''' MIC2026-2BM (0140) Dual-Channel Power Distribution Switches], a '''NTK''' 6.000MHz oscillator, <small>and some other stuff</small>.
This hub includes two extra back plastic covers for the device.. *Clear *Opaque-White The stock cover is a translucent grey color.
The power supply included with the unit appears to be a '''Comda''' AD1505C (100-240VAC ~ 0.5A, 47-63Hz -> 4.0-5.5VDC, 2.1A / 10.5W maximum).
The manual specifies that... *the included USB cable is a F3U133-06. *the device weighs [[Weight::158g]] and has dimensions of [[Dimensions::108 mm x 95 mm x 32 mm]]. *the operation temperature range is specified as ~ 5 to 40 degrees Celsius. **relative humidity range of 0 to 80% (non-condensing) *the storage temperature range is specified as ~ -20 to 60 degrees Celsius. *each port provides a maximum of 500mA @ 5V. *the specced power supply is 5VDC, 2.6A (differing from the PSU included with the unit).. *the copyright year is 2001 (which jives with the year on the box).
